===Etymology===
From {{etyl|la}} {{term|sub||under, beneath|lang=la}} + {{term|fixus|lang=la}}, perfect passive participle of {{term|figere||to fasten, fix|lang=la}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{qualifier|noun}} {{IPA|/ˈsʌfɪks/}}
* {{audio|en-us-suffix.ogg|Audio (US)}}
* {{qualifier|verb}} {{IPA|/ˈsʌfɪks/|/səˈfɪks/}}
* {{rhymes|ɪks}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|es}}

# One or more letters or sounds added at the end of a word to modify the word's meaning, such as ''able'', which changes ''sing'' into ''singable'', for example.

====Usage notes====
* The plural {{term|suffices|lang=en}} occasionally appears (including in one educational publication), but it is not a standard Latin plural.

